org.iiitb.model.bean
Class DivisibleMemoryUnit

java.lang.Object
  org.iiitb.model.bean.MemoryUnit
      org.iiitb.model.bean.DivisibleMemoryUnit

public class DivisibleMemoryUnit
extends MemoryUnit

Models a logical sub-unit of memoryMemory) that is further divisible. It is composed of sub-units(IndivisibleMemoryUnit) which are indivisible.

Typically this class should be sub classed to suit the specific memory management scheme being designed, viz, paged segmentation, segmented paging or kernel memory management scheme

public DivisibleMemoryUnit(long address,

                           boolean allocated)
Initialises a DivisibleMemoryUnit object. The memory unit this object represents can be seen as capable of further division into IndivisibleMemoryUnit's. Right now, it consists of just one IndivisibleMemoryUnit object which spans the entire size

Parameters:
address - Start address
size - Size
allocated - Indicates if this memory unit has been allocated or not.

public void insert(IndivisibleMemoryUnit mu)

Insert an indivisible memory unit into this divisible memory unit.

Parameters:
mu - The memory unit to be inserted.
Throws:
InvalidMemoryUnitAllocationRequestException - The specified MemoryUnit is invalid. One of the following things could be the cause
1. No holes(free chunks) at required address
2. The hole at the required address is not big enough
